      "judge_reason": "subprocess.run is called with 'tar' as a partial path (no absolute path). An attacker who can control PATH or place a malicious 'tar' executable earlier in the search path could execute arbitrary code. Additionally, the filepath argument is user-controlled, making command injection possible even with list-based invocation if the argument contains shell metacharacters (tar may interpret them)."
